revision.revremark:
Summary of changes:


  Move aside all books except for Linux
  Fundamentals;

  Change the title of the book to Linux Doesn't Have
  to Be Hard: A Beginner's Guide and the title of the series
  to Userbie;

  Move aside all minibooks except for First Steps on
  the Command Line;

  Change the title of the minibook to 45 Minutes to
  Get Started on the Command Line: A Linux Primer;

  Reword the explanation of the cat
  command;

  Modify the examples to refrain from using the
  cat command before its usage is explained to the
  reader;

  Modify the examples to refrain from using a
  semicolon – ';' before
  its usage is explained to the reader;

  Copy the description of the echo command
  from the chapter on shell arguments;

  Remove the exercise that relies on understanding the meaning
  of an asterisk – '*',
  given that it is not yet explained by that point;

  Remove the chapter on the file system tree from
  45 Minutes to Get Started on the Command Line,
  with the intention of putting it into another minibook;

  Remove the section on the rename command
  from 45 Minutes to Get Started on the Command Line,
  with the intention of putting it into another minibook;

  Modify the titles to use a consistent convention for
  capitalisation and special characters;

  Replace selected external links with userbie.com;

  Add the missing Addendum to the Free Documentation
  License;

  Modify the abstract and add a preface;

  Implement the [feedback] link;

  Modify the license notice to strictly use version 1.3 of the
  Free Documentation License only, with Aleksander Korzynski as the proxy
  for deciding if a later version can be used;

  Modify the license notice to make the
  Preface an Invariant section;

  Display the license notice prominently in the abstract, the
  LICENSE file and the appendix containing the full
  text of the license;

  Use the command git describe --tags
  to generate the version string of the book;

  Modify the build scripts to save the publisher name in the
  book metadata;

  Create a site-specific CSS file to be replaced by a site
  owner;

  Change the command used to generate a PDF file from
  build to pdf;

  Use xsltproc instead of
  xmlto as the command to invoke the XSLT
  processor;

  Improve error handling in the make
  script;

  Modify the make script to generate unique
  IDs for book parts and chapters;

  Various bug fixes and finishing touches;



